<plot>Inspired by the stories of Argentine writer Julio Cortazar, yet blended with the realities of contemporary Argentina, Wind in Our Hair is an experimental narrative directed by New York filmmaker Lynne Sachs about four girls discovering themselves through a fascination with the trains that pass by their house. A story of early-teen anticipation and disappointment, the film is circumscribed by a period of profound Argentine political and social unrest.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?657806</url></doc>
